            <h2>About the Book</h2>
            <p>
                <b>Poezii</b> is a remarkable collection of poems that showcases the extraordinary talent of Romania's 
                greatest poet, <u>Mihai Eminescu</u>. The title translates to <i>Poems</i> in English, representing one 
                of the most significant literary works in Romanian culture. This collection captures the essence of 
                romantic poetry, blending deep philosophical reflections with lyrical beauty.
            </p>

            <div class="book-image">
                <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mihai_Eminescu" title="Learn more about Mihai Eminescu on Wikipedia">
                    <img src="img.jpeg" alt="Book cover of Poezii by Mihai Eminescu" title="Click to open Wikipedia">
                </a>
            </div>

            <p>
                The poems in this collection explore themes of love, nature, spirituality, and the human condition. 
                Each verse is crafted with meticulous attention to language and form, making <b>Poezii</b> an 
                essential read for anyone interested in 19th-century European poetry. For a deeper understanding of 
                the historical context and literary significance of these works, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mihai_Eminescu">
                I recommend visiting the comprehensive Wikipedia article about Mihai Eminescu</a>.
            </p>

            <div class="quote">
