        <div class="biography-section">
            <h2>The Author: Mihai Eminescu</h2>
            <p>
                <u>Mihai Eminescu</u> (1850-1889) was a Romantic poet, philosopher, and journalist who is 
                regarded as the most important Romanian writer and poet of all time. Born in Botoşani, Eminescu 
                spent much of his youth traveling across Europe, which profoundly influenced his literary voice. 
                His works are characterized by a melancholic depth, intricate metaphors, and a profound engagement 
                with existential questions.
            </p>

            <p>
                Despite his brief life cut short by mental illness, Eminescu left behind a legacy that defined 
                Romanian literature and influenced generations of poets and writers. His poems, collected in 
                <b>Poezii</b>, remain widely celebrated and studied in schools and universities throughout Romania 
                and beyond. The depth of his imagination and the beauty of his language continue to captivate 
                readers more than a century after his death.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="legacy-section">
            <h2>Literary Legacy</h2>
            <p>
                The <b>Poezii</b> collection stands as a testament to Eminescu's genius and continues to be a source 
                of inspiration for artists, musicians, and writers. His influence extends far beyond Romania, with his 
                works translated into numerous languages and studied in academic institutions worldwide. The themes he 
                explored—love, loss, nature, and the search for meaning—remain eternally relevant.
            </p>

            <div class="quote">
                "I have loved you in a thousand different forms and I will love you in a thousand more..."
            </div>

            <p>
                Reading <b>Poezii</b> is not merely an engagement with historical literature; it is a journey into 
                the human soul. Eminescu's poems invite readers to reflect on their own experiences and emotions, 
                making each reading a deeply personal experience. Whether you are a student of literature or simply 
                a lover of beautiful words, this collection offers profound insights and unforgettable verses that 
                will stay with you long after you finish reading.
            </p>
